lead_paragraph: World champion Vivian Cheruiyot booked her ticket to Rio Games while Olympic silver medalist Sally Kipyego became the first major scalp in the two-day Kenyan Olympic trials which kicked off on Thursday.

headline.print_headline: Kenya's Cheruiyot Books Rio Berth, Kipyego Falters
